<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4597: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Minister in Portugal</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Magruder</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-20T19:00:00-04:00">July 20, 1931—7 p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                                <p>16. Your telegram No. 24, July 19, 1 p.m. As no public
                                    announcement has been made of the Portuguese acceptance of the
                                    President’s proposal, and as its adherence has not been
                                    communicated to this Government, I deem it unnecessary to
                                    deliver the message contained in the Department’s telegram No.
                                    14, July 3, 2 p.m., but shall instruct you further if and when
                                    such announcement is made.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>